=\"fn\">G</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">A</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Subfunctor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Subfunctor.toFunctor\">toFunctor</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">w</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.CategoryStruct.comp\">CategoryStruct.comp</a> <span class=\"fn\">φ</span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.CategoryStruct.comp\">CategoryStruct.comp</a> <span class=\"fn\">φ</span> <span class=\"fn\">g</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">G</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Subfunctor/Equalizer.html#CategoryTheory.Subfunctor.equalizer\">Subfunctor.equalizer</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">g</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Subfunctor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Subfunctor.toFunctor\">toFunctor</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"**Alias** of `CategoryTheory.Subfunctor.equalizer.lift`.\n\n---\n\nGiven two morphisms `f` and `g` in `A.toFunctor ⟶ F₂`, if `φ : G ⟶ A.toFunctor`\nis such that `φ ≫ f = φ ≫ g`, then this is the lifted morphism\n`G ⟶ (Subfunctor.equalizer f g).toFunctor`. This is part of the universal\nproperty of the equalizer that is satisfied by\nthe functor `(Subfunctor.equalizer f g).toFunctor`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Subfunctor/Equalizer.html#CategoryTheory.Subfunctor.Subpresheaf.equalizer.lift","kind":"def","line":137,"name":"CategoryTheory.Subfunctor.Subpresheaf.equalizer.lift","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d0